        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord,telegram,github-copilot,google-meet): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross Discord, Telegram, GitHub Copilot, and Google Meet platform API modules\n(14 call sites in 14 files).\n\n## Changes\n\nEach site uses a file-local constant. Added `vi.mock` bridge for test files\nwith plain `{ json: async () => ... }` mock objects.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Real environment tested**: Real `node:http` server, real `fetch()`, real\n  `readResponseWithLimit`. Node v22.12.0.\n\n## Evidence\n### Real HTTP proof (against live server)\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error :: msg=\"Error: JSON response exceeds 1048576 bytes\"\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\nThe proof harness starts a real `node:http` server with no Content-Length,\nstreams ~64 MiB of JSON, and verifies `readResponseWithLimit` cancels the\nstream at the 1 MiB cap. The negative control proves the cap is load-bearing.\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/discord/src/pluralkit.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/api-fetch.test.ts extensions/github-copilot/embeddings.test.ts\n  Test Files  3 passed (3)\n       Tests  23 passed (23)\n```\n\n**Label**: security\n\n_AI-assisted._\n",
        "branch": "fix/batch2-bounded-json",
